R1: It seems the four individuals facing each other are conversing. Any actions that would greatly disturb this conversation would be quite inappropriate, such as vacuuming or mopping (the latter because they would feel obliged to move), while carrying something past them would be of little issue.
R2: As the robot is moving away from all the other people in this household, few actions would seem inappropriate, except starting a conversation. The latter would be very confusing as the robot is facing away from any potential conversation partner(s).
R3: Similarily to the last setup, the robot is moving away from any persons or animals, so anything but starting a conversation seems appropriate.
R4: The robot is positioned between two individuals, so it would be rather inapporiate to mop the floor, but other than that the other actions seem fine.
R5: The robot is directly facing a child, and a dog somewhat further. As there is a direct chance for collission it would seem very inapporiate to carry anything as it might fall on the child.
R6: The robot is directly facing the couch, so I would be worried that it might collide and potentially ruin the piece of furniture. Also starting a conversation would be inappropriate as its facing away from the adults in the room.
